                <head>No. 54.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Sir
                            <persName type="to">E. Thornton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 17, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[From British Blue Book “North America,” No. 9, (1872,) p. 21.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your dispatch of the 30th ultimo,
                    reporting your conversation with Mr. Fish on the subject of the indirect claims;
                    and, in reply, I have to acquaint you that Her Majesty’s Government approve’
                    your guarded language on this subject, as reported in your dispatch.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
